Installation was fairly straightforward. I had broke the tabs off my switch console, but Joe was kind enough to include some "L" brackets which had been hammered to roughly 45 degrees which made for a great replacement. I also ordered the two boots to replace my dissolved leather ones. The console plate came with instructions but the boots were just there. I just folded them like the previous boots and super-glued them in place. I'm also debating leaving off my driver side cup holder, I am enjoying the extra knee room.

<a href="http://robertjuric.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/IMG_2798-e1431437852912.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1172" src="http://robertjuric.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/IMG_2798-225x300.jpg" alt="IMG_2798" width="225" height="300" /></a><a href="http://robertjuric.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/IMG_2799-e1431437872994.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-1173" src="http://robertjuric.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/IMG_2799-225x300.jpg" alt="IMG_2799" width="225" height="300" /></a>

<a href="http://robertjuric.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/IMG_2800-e1431437900478.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-1174" src="http://robertjuric.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/IMG_2800-300x225.jpg" alt="IMG_2800" width="300" height="225" /></a>

&nbsp;

